Abdullahi Ganduje, governor of Kano, is making efforts to stop the defection of Abdulmumin Jibrin, former house of representatives member, from the All Progressives Congress (APC). On Saturday, Jibrin said he was going to announce his new political party, adding that he has done his best for the party. The former lawmaker is the director-general of Tinubu support group. In a statement on Sunday, Abdullahi Abbas, APC chairman, said Ganduje has asked that the crisis among those seeking to represent Kiru/Bebeji federal constituency be resolved. 